<center><h1 style="background-color:red"> CHICKEN 65!!! </h1></center>
<center><h2 style="background-color:orange">This dish is perfect for spice lovers!</h2></center>
<center><img src="http://www.watscooking.com/images/dish/large/chicken_652.png"
style="width:700px;height:500px;"></center>

<h3 style="color:blue;"> Ingredients </h3>
</body>
<p>300 gm chicken breast, cleaned and cut into small cubes (boneless)</p>
<p>½ cup buttermilk</p>
<p>½ tsp Kashmiri chilli powder </p>
<p>½ tsp cumin powder</p>
<p>¼ tsp black pepper powder</p>
<p>½ tsp turmeric powder</p>
<p>1 cup shredded Swiss or Cheddar cheese </p>
<p>1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese</p>
<p>½ tsp coriander powder</p>
<p>2 tsp ginger garlic paste</p>
<p>2 tsp rice flour or corn flour</p>
<p>A handful of curry leaves</p>
<p>2-3 cups of oil</p>
<p>1 tsp vinegar (optional)</p>
<p style="color:Red;">STEP 1:</p>
<p>Mix the yogurt with all the spices, corn flour, ginger-garlic paste, and some salt.After mixing, add the chicken pieces.</p>
<p style="color:Red;">STEP 2:</p>
<p>Refrigerate this mixture for about 2 hours to let it marinade or</p>
<p style="color:Red;">STEP 3:</p>
<p> Heat the oil in a pan. The oil should be enough to almost cover the pieces.</p>
<p style="color:Red;">STEP 4:</p>
<p>Gently add the marinated chicken pieces one by one and fry on a medium-low flame until golden brown.Turn it every once in a while</p>
<p style="color:Red;">STEP 5:</p>
<p>Add curry leaves to the fried pieces of chicken.</p>
<p style="color:Red;">STEP 6:</p>
<p> Garnish with parsley and serve hot with lemon wedges and raw sliced onions</p>
<center><p style="color:Blue;">Enjoy the meal!</p></center>
